  <lemma xml:id="lecture-notes-lem-slide-and-divide">
    <title>Slide and Divide</title>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Let <m>ax^2 + bx + c = 0</m> with <m>a \ne 0</m>.
        To perform slide-and-divide, follow these steps:
      </p>
      <p>
        <ol>
          <li><p>Rewrite the equation as <m>x^2 + bx + ac = 0</m>. (This is the slide step.)</p></li>
          <li><p>Factor using the <m>ac</m>-method as <m>(x + c_1)(x + c_2) = 0</m>.</p></li>
          <li><p>Divide the values of <m>c_1</m> and <m>c_2</m> by <m>a</m> to get <m>\left(x - \frac{c_1}{a}\right)\left(x - \frac{c_2}{a}\right) = 0</m>.</p></li>
          <li><p>Simplify the fractions.</p></li>
          <li><p>Use the Zero Product Property to solve for <m>x</m>.</p></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </statement>
  </lemma>

